abstract: An organized base of grass-roots power is the key to passing gun reform laws.
snippet: An organized base of grass-roots power is the key to passing gun reform laws.
lead_paragraph: Is helpless outrage the only choice gun-control advocates have after Las Vegas? As the horrific news unfolded, share prices of major gun manufacturers rose. Market investors were trading on the ugly reality we all knew: Gun regulations would not change, but fear of them would drive sales.

abstract: Mr. Geffen lamented the downsizing of the $500 million David Geffen Hall project at Lincoln Center. “New York should have the best of everything,” he said.
snippet: Mr. Geffen lamented the downsizing of the $500 million David Geffen Hall project at Lincoln Center. “New York should have the best of everything,” he said.
lead_paragraph: The media mogul David Geffen, one of the cultural world’s leading philanthropists, attacked wealthy New Yorkers on Wednesday for what he called a “shameful” record of failing to donate to the city’s concert halls and allowing these institutions to downsize their ambitions.

abstract: At a congressional hearing on Tuesday, Equifax’s former chief executive called on competitors to offer free credit locks for life. Experian declined to do so.
snippet: At a congressional hearing on Tuesday, Equifax’s former chief executive called on competitors to offer free credit locks for life. Experian declined to do so.
lead_paragraph: When Equifax’s recently retired chief executive, Richard F. Smith, appeared before a panel of the House Energy and Commerce Committee Tuesday, he held himself out as a changed man.

abstract: Prosecutors said about half of the 30 people charged in the scam parked in spaces reserved for city agencies, like the Fire Department and Department of Health.
snippet: Prosecutors said about half of the 30 people charged in the scam parked in spaces reserved for city agencies, like the Fire Department and Department of Health.
lead_paragraph: Thirty people were hauled into state court on Tuesday in handcuffs and charged with using fake parking placards made to look like city-issued documents to park in special zones and to avoid paying tickets.

lead_paragraph: The political news cycle is fast, and keeping up can be overwhelming. Trying to find differing perspectives worth your time is even harder. That’s why we have scoured the internet for political writing from the right and left that you might not have seen.

abstract: The center and the New York Philharmonic announced they would seek simpler ways to improve a hall they have long wanted to change.
snippet: The center and the New York Philharmonic announced they would seek simpler ways to improve a hall they have long wanted to change.
lead_paragraph: One of the biggest cultural building projects in the country was sent back to the drawing board on Tuesday, when the new leaders of Lincoln Center and the New York Philharmonic announced they were scuttling a half-billion-dollar plan for a gut renovation of David Geffen Hall and seeking simpler ways to improve the lackluster theater.

abstract: Cynthia Brann will become the new correction commissioner in New York, disappointing some who wanted an outside set of eyes on a troubled agency.
snippet: Cynthia Brann will become the new correction commissioner in New York, disappointing some who wanted an outside set of eyes on a troubled agency.
lead_paragraph: After months of searching around the country for a new correction commissioner, Mayor Bill de Blasio announced on Tuesday that he had found the person to head the Correction Department, which oversees the troubled Rikers Island jail complex, from within its own ranks.

abstract: A showdown looms at the ride-hailing company after its co-founder Travis Kalanick responded to a proposal to limit his power by naming two new directors.
snippet: A showdown looms at the ride-hailing company after its co-founder Travis Kalanick responded to a proposal to limit his power by naming two new directors.
lead_paragraph: Travis Kalanick staged a power play at Uber late last week, and a showdown with the company’s board could come as soon as Tuesday.
